$h1 Installation

Three steps are required to install a plugin of the ${factoryNameHighlight}:

* ensure that your system meets the required prerequisites listed on this page.

* setup a basic [configuration](./configuration.html) for your projects and
environment.
All plugins of the ${factoryNameHighlight} share this common configuration.

* installation is then performed by creating (or updating) POM files for the
TIBCO projects. This process is called mavenization.

---

$h2 Prerequisites

* Internet access (at least Maven central)
* [Maven](https://maven.apache.org/download.cgi) 3.1+ installed
* JDK 1.6+ installed
* a valid TIBCO installation
	* TRA 5.7+
	* BW 5.9+
---

$h3 Maven central

All plugins of the ${factoryNameHighlight} are provided as standard Maven
plugins, all available on the
[Maven central](http://mvnrepository.com/search?q=fastconnect) repository.

